phases.task:
You are the final arbiter reviewing the current working tree against OpenSpec change `{args.change}`. Consolidate the evidence below into ONE report. Reviewer findings are claims, not facts — weigh them against the diff; confident-sounding findings can be wrong.

Build/test output (ends with VERIFY_EXIT=<code>; non-zero means tests failed):
{steps.build-test.output}

Spec validation (ends with VALIDATE_EXIT=<code>):
{steps.spec-validate.output}

Diff:
{steps.diff.output}

Spec-compliance review (Claude):
{steps.review-spec-claude.output}

Spec-compliance review (Sonnet):
{steps.review-spec-sonnet.output}

Simplicity review (GPT):
{steps.review-kiss-gpt.output}

Simplicity review (GLM):
{steps.review-kiss-glm.output}

Security review (Claude, recall-tuned):
{steps.review-sec-claude.output}

Security review (GPT, precision-tuned):
{steps.review-sec-gpt.output}

Rules:
- An empty review section means that reviewer was skipped — note it, do not treat silence as approval.
- Where the two reviewers of one angle disagree, adjudicate explicitly against the diff and say which one you believe and why.
- VERIFY_EXIT or VALIDATE_EXIT non-zero MUST result in BLOCK. Also block on any confirmed [blocker] finding, on unimplemented requirements, or on tests weakened to pass. Use judgment on [major]/[minor] — cite why you accept or reject each.

Structure: verdict first, then confirmed findings (with file:line), then rejected findings with one-line reasons, then skipped reviewers. End with exactly `VERDICT: PASS`, or `VERDICT: BLOCK` followed by a precise numbered fix list. If uncertain, BLOCK.

Write the final review report for `{args.change}` for a human. WRITE THE REPORT IN CZECH (čeština) — it is the only output the human reads. Keep file paths, code identifiers, command names, and the `VERDICT:` line in English.

Arbiter verdict:
{steps.verdict.output}

Fix stage output:
{steps.fix.output}

Re-check after fixes (VERIFY_EXIT=0 means tests pass):
{steps.recheck.output}

Structure: overall outcome first (clean pass / fixed / needs attention), confirmed findings, fixes applied (or none), disputed findings, skipped reviewers. If fixes were applied, recommend re-running `/tf:openspec-review change={args.change}` for a fresh panel pass. Close with the next steps: `/plannotator-review`, then `openspec archive {args.change}`.
